ASSEMBLY JOINT RESOLUTION—Condemning the attack on the U.S. Capitol
on January 6, 2021, including the assault on law enforcement officers,
and denouncing the use of presidential pardons and commutations to
absolve the participants in the riot.
1 WHEREAS, On January 6, 2021, a mob violently overpowered the U.S. Capitol
2 Police and breached the U.S. Capitol, disrupting the peaceful transfer of power; and
3 WHEREAS, This insurrection was not only an attack on the U.S. Capitol, but on
4 the rule of law, the values of American democracy and the U.S. Constitution, which
5 are the very foundations of the American Republic; and
6 WHEREAS, The U.S. Capitol Police, alongside other law enforcement agencies,
7 demonstrated heroism and unwavering courage, professionalism and commitment
8 to their duties while protecting members of Congress and others within the U.S.
9 Capitol during the attack, which resulted in traumatic injuries to at least 140 law
10 enforcement officers in the line of duty; and
11 WHEREAS, President Donald Trump’s granting of pardons and commutations
12 on January 20, 2025, to the roughly 1,500 criminals involved in the attack is an act
13 of betrayal not only to the law enforcement officers who risked their lives on
14 January 6, 2021, but to all U.S. citizens; and
15 WHEREAS, Among those criminals was one who assaulted D.C. Metropolitan
16 Police Department Officer Noah Rathbun with a flagpole, another who repeatedly
17 pressed a stun gun into the neck of D.C. Metropolitan Police Department Officer

