1 Michael Fanone and another who sprayed multiple law enforcement officers with
2 bear spray; and
3 WHEREAS, The International Association of Chiefs of Police and the Fraternal
4 Order of Police jointly condemned these presidential pardons and commutations,
5 emphasizing that crimes against law enforcement officers are attacks on society and
6 undermine the rule of law and that failure to hold perpetrators of violent crimes
7 against law enforcement officers accountable may embolden others to commit
8 similar acts of violence; now, therefore, be it
9 RESOLVED BY THE ASSEMBLY AND SENATE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, JOINTLY,
10 That the members of the 83rd session of the Nevada Legislature condemn the attack
11 on the U.S. Capitol on January 6, 2021, including the assault on law enforcement
12 officers, and denounce the use of presidential pardons and commutations to absolve
13 the participants in the riot; and be it further
14 RESOLVED, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly prepare and transmit a copy
15 of this resolution to the President of the United States, the President Pro Tempore
16 of the United States Senate, the Speaker of the United States House of
17 Representatives and the members of the Nevada Congressional Delegation; and be
18 it further
19 RESOLVED, That this resolution becomes effective upon passage.

